{"id":26,"date":"2016-07-07T16:14:47","date_gmt":"2016-07-07T15:14:47","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/prep\/music-and-drama\/"},"modified":"2021-12-14T14:35:06","modified_gmt":"2021-12-14T14:35:06","slug":"music-and-drama","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/prep\/music-and-drama\/","title":{"rendered":"Music and Drama"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>The vibrant Music department in the Prep school allows all students to experience a variety of music from different countries, genres and periods in history. Their experience in the classroom enables them to play a range of instruments, improvise, compose, sing and explore music technology using software such as Mixcraft and Cubase.<\/p>\n<p>Singing is at the heart of our Music Department. All Prep students are involved in a Choir, including our Key Stage 1 Choir and Key Stage 2 Choir. We have a Year 6 Gospel Choir who compete and perform in local festivals such as the Tunbridge Wells Music Festival. Singing is such an important skill and, as all the students are involved, it gives them exciting opportunities to perform in big school events, such as the \u2018Celebration of Song\u2019, the annual Carol Concert, and the Winter Concert in which they team up with the Senior School Choir for a fantastic finale.<\/p>\n<p>All students who play an instrument are strongly encouraged to join our extra-curricular programme. We have a Prep Rock Band, a combined Prep and Senior School Orchestra and Jazz band. The instrumentalists also get opportunities to perform in assemblies, informal tea concerts and more formal evening concerts including the Prep Soiree.<\/p>\n<p>Music and Drama work closely together to produce Christmas Nativities and the annual Summer show, with recent acclaimed performances such as \u2018Joseph and the Technicolour Dreamcoat\u2019, \u2018Shakespeare Rocks\u2019, \u2018Robin and the Sherwood Hoodies\u2019 and &#8216;The Lion King&#8217;.<\/p>\n<p>The Music department has a team of 12 visiting instrumental teachers, offering tuition for voice and a wide variety of instruments. With these we enter students into ABRSM exams in which we have a 100% pass rate. We also run external workshops including a violin programme for Year 2s, a World Percussion Day for the whole of the Prep School and a weekly percussion \u2018Drum and Fun\u2019 session held by our percussion teacher Richmond Stockwell.<\/p>\n<p>Students that show a particular talent and commitment to Music can apply for Music Scholarships for entry into the Senior School.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-9520\" src=\"https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/Year-7-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"319\" height=\"240\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/Year-7-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/Year-7.jpg 640w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 319px) 100vw, 319px\" \/> <img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-8827\" src=\"https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/P1010401-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"356\" height=\"237\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/P1010401-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/P1010401-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/P1010401-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/P1010401-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/P1010401-570x380.jpg 570w, https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/P1010401.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 356px) 100vw, 356px\" \/>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\" wp-image-6444\" src=\"https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/10\/IMG_5612-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"361\" height=\"240\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/10\/IMG_5612-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/